<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="87">
In the MNCN three lots are labelled ' 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1777" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1777" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimus aristaceus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="87" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aristaceus">Bulimus aristaceus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Crosse’">Crosse'</normalizedToken>
which are considered as syntypes. These lots appear not to be conspecific, and only lot MNCN 15.05/7180 is considered as type material of this taxon. As Crosse did not state on how many specimens his description was based, but no material of this species is present in the Paris collection, the sole specimen is now designated lectotype (design. n.) to fixate the taxon. The figure of 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosse, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal de Conchyliogie" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" pagination="97 - 109" title="Descriptions d'especes nouvelles." volume="18" year="1870">Crosse (1870)</bibRefCitation>
does not entirely adequately represent the current state of the shell as the colour marks may largely have faded away. 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosse, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal de Conchyliogie," pageId="6" pageNumber="91" pagination="312 - 318" title="Note sur les coquilles terrestres recueillies par M. le professeur Orton dans la region superieure de l'Amazone et descriptions d'especes nouvelles." volume="19" year="1871">Crosse (1871)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned a variety, collected &quot;Route de Quito 
<normalizedToken originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
Napo (prof. Orton)&quot;; this would indicate that this species might occur on the eastern slopes of the Cordillera, but we have not seen this material.
</paragraph>
